                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13614609" author="svenmeier" created="Tue, 26 Mar 2013 22:11:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Has this ever been the case, i.e. is this a bug or enhancement?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615018" author="sclassen" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 08:16:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this used to work in 1.5. thats how i found this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
after switching to wicket 6 some of my ${label} were not replaced any more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615115" author="svenmeier" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 11:00:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With Wicket 6 we had an API break for IErrorMessageSource:&lt;br/&gt;
So variables in the default message are no longer resolved, i.e. the default message is taken as is.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can do variable resolving yourself though:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/wicket/blob/wicket-1.5.x/wicket-core/src/main/java/org/apache/wicket/validation/IErrorMessageSource.java#L57&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/wicket/blob/wicket-1.5.x/wicket-core/src/main/java/org/apache/wicket/validation/IErrorMessageSource.java#L57&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/wicket/blob/wicket-1.5.x/wicket-core/src/main/java/org/apache/wicket/markup/html/form/FormComponent.java#L201&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/wicket/blob/wicket-1.5.x/wicket-core/src/main/java/org/apache/wicket/markup/html/form/FormComponent.java#L201&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615151" author="sclassen" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 12:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated my project to use addKey and substitution works for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If wicket 6 will not do substitution for setMessage it would be nice if you could state this in the javadoc of the ValidationError class and the setMessage method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13615160" author="svenmeier" created="Wed, 27 Mar 2013 12:11:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You&apos;re right, I&apos;ve added a note to ValidationError#setMessage(). Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
